The employee behind the counter was very rude, not sure if he was the owner or not. Today 12/11/2020 around 4:30pm I walked in, picked up a menu & sat down to decide what I wanted. When he was done with the order he was making & those customers left I walked to the counter & began placing my order. I wanted a #3 combo a sweet & savory crepe with a soda. As I was talking to him & adding what I wanted to my crepes another customer walks up, interrupts me and starts talking to him in Spanish, ignoring me as if I'm not standing there already talking to him. The employee begins to have a conversation with him in Spanish & leaves from behind the counter to talk with him by the door. When I interrupted them & said "Excuse me. You don't see me standing here talking to him? You're just going to ignore me & talk to him as if I'm not placing an order & about to be a paying customer?" The customer waves his hand at me & gives a horrible version of I'm sorry. The employee comes back behind the the counter & apologizes, but I'm already ticked off at this point. I said "F*ck that I'm not giving you my money for rude service" and I left. My order was only $15 maybe $17 after tax, the amount is irrelevant. If you need to interrupt someone, especially a paying customer you say "Excuse me, please give me a minute." I took my $15 and went a couple block over to Baja Fresh when my business is valued.
